Meet Jordan Collier

29 Jan 2013

[caption id=”attachment_1375” align=”alignnone” width=”300’][/caption]

Hey everyone!

I’m a third year medical student at Pacific Northwest University of Health Sciences, home of the Mighty Mustangs! I currently live in Mount Vernon, WA and am stumbling along as a Junior Doctor…my wife’s most endearing pet name…at Skagit Valley Hospital.

I am very happily married to my beautiful and creative wife, Laura, who gave me the world’s cutest and strongest-willed kid, Parker J. Life as a daddy, husband, medical student, friend, son, sibling and more…can be a bit hectic, but I love my life and am so blessed.

The great state of Washington has always been my home, living in Kent, Seattle, Yakima, and now in Mount Vernon. I did have a quick stint in Granada, Spain while a junior at the University of Washington…Go Dawgs!!…and subsequently got bit by the travel bug, which unfortunately isn’t too conducive with the med student lifestyle and non-existent salary.

I can’t claim the prestigeous title of Geek, like my Unchart.com superiors, but hopefully they can help me change that. I did grow up in the world of dial-up AOL, giving me madd middle-school AIM flirting skillz, and I was in undergrad when TheFacebook made its debut. I like computers and I kind of know how to use them. Let’s do this!
